WEBVTT

00:00.046 --> 00:01.252
<i>Previously on "Suits"...</i>

00:01.276 --> 00:02.063
It's a no.

00:02.064 --> 00:03.305
I thought you liked the idea.

00:03.329 --> 00:04.530
That was before I realized

00:04.531 --> 00:06.431
that it was nothing but
sassy remarks.

00:06.467 --> 00:08.178
I thought you wanted our baby
to have a relationship

00:08.202 --> 00:10.168
with its biological father.
If you're gonna get

00:10.204 --> 00:13.939
this worked up, it makes me
think I don't really know you.

00:13.974 --> 00:15.285
What if I could make it
more like you?

00:15.309 --> 00:16.753
I might be able
to give it the ability

00:16.777 --> 00:18.355
to learn from your heart.
You really think

00:18.379 --> 00:20.012
we could do that?
We can try.

00:20.047 --> 00:22.147
Rachel Zane deserves to be
in the Bar.

00:22.182 --> 00:24.016
You're not only gonna
stop blocking her,

00:24.051 --> 00:26.585
you're gonna run interference
for her if someone else does.

00:26.620 --> 00:28.253
And in return,
you'll do what I want.

00:28.288 --> 00:30.789
No, but I'll do what you want
for something else.

00:30.824 --> 00:32.101
We need to come up
with a lawsuit

00:32.125 --> 00:33.992
against Velocity Data Solutions.
No.

00:34.028 --> 00:35.639
- What do you mean, "no"?
- Fabricating a lawsuit

00:35.663 --> 00:37.262
to manipulate a stock
is illegal.

00:37.297 --> 00:39.264
It's not illegal if we find
a legitimate suit.

00:39.299 --> 00:41.444
Let's finish the job and get you
back to being a lawyer.

00:41.468 --> 00:43.535
"Tenants are required
to be notified

00:43.570 --> 00:45.937
of all construction
by certified letter."

00:45.973 --> 00:47.839
Is this a certified letter
or not?

00:47.875 --> 00:49.074
- Objection.
- Your Honor,

00:49.109 --> 00:51.109
this is the fraudulent attorney.
Open your mouth

00:51.145 --> 00:53.111
in my courtroom again
and you will be removed.

00:53.147 --> 00:55.180
Mr. Grady, do you have
an objection or not?

00:55.215 --> 00:56.948
- I don't.
- Then the court has no choice

00:56.984 --> 01:00.218
but to dismiss this case
with prejudice.

01:00.254 --> 01:02.187
The guy holding up your
interview was trying

01:02.222 --> 01:04.589
to get us to do something
because he thought he could.

01:04.625 --> 01:07.159
- Are you going to?
- Yes.

01:07.194 --> 01:08.627
He is.
Are you saying

01:08.662 --> 01:11.563
what I think you're saying?
I'm in.

01:14.301 --> 01:15.701
Okay, Rachel's gone.

01:15.736 --> 01:17.113
I don't want any bullshit.
You're telling me

01:17.137 --> 01:18.503
that no matter what we do,

01:18.539 --> 01:20.038
Rachel's getting into the Bar?

01:20.074 --> 01:22.374
What I'm telling you is
if she doesn't get in,

01:22.409 --> 01:25.243
that asshole isn't gonna be
the one that stopped her.

01:27.247 --> 01:30.449
Okay. I'm in.

01:30.484 --> 01:32.484
What do we have to do?

01:32.519 --> 01:34.297
I told you what we need to do.
We need to make a dent

01:34.321 --> 01:36.988
in Velocity Data's stock.
Harvey, that's no joke.

01:37.024 --> 01:38.735
You realize how much we're gonna
have to sue them for

01:38.759 --> 01:40.070
to make their earnings
take a hit?

01:40.094 --> 01:41.094
You're damn right I do.

01:41.128 --> 01:43.428
They're a huge company,
which means

01:43.464 --> 01:44.507
it's got to be something huge.

01:44.531 --> 01:45.709
I don't even know
if that matters.

01:45.733 --> 01:46.843
No matter what we sue them for,

01:46.867 --> 01:47.911
they're just gonna
want to settle.

01:47.935 --> 01:49.768
I know that.
Which means we need to insist

01:49.803 --> 01:51.570
on an admission of guilt.

01:51.605 --> 01:54.005
I get it.

01:54.041 --> 01:56.086
You want me to run this whole
thing through the clinic.

01:56.110 --> 01:59.044
It's the only way to make it
look legitimate.

01:59.079 --> 02:02.547
Harvey, I don't know if I can
convince Nathan to do that.

02:02.583 --> 02:04.716
Well, you better,
because if anyone figures out

02:04.752 --> 02:06.651
that we're doing this
for personal gain,

02:06.687 --> 02:09.554
your chance of
getting into the bar is gone.

02:13.694 --> 02:17.529
Wait, you were Captain
of the Glee Club?

02:17.564 --> 02:18.942
The official title
is Lieutenant Colonel,

02:18.966 --> 02:20.043
but that's cool
you didn't know that.

02:20.067 --> 02:22.334
Mm-hmm.

02:22.369 --> 02:26.238
Oh, my God. You still
had braces at 17.

02:26.273 --> 02:28.774
Actually, I had them again
at 28.

02:28.809 --> 02:30.108
Wow.

02:30.144 --> 02:33.612
Between this,
your nasal passages,

02:33.647 --> 02:35.847
the skin tag epidemic
and the foot surgeries,

02:35.883 --> 02:37.749
you really had a lot
of medical procedures.

02:37.785 --> 02:39.229
Tara, I know what you
must be thinking

02:39.253 --> 02:40.986
and I swear,

02:41.021 --> 02:42.988
I will not pass any of my
maladies onto our child.

02:43.023 --> 02:45.657
Louis,
I wasn't thinking that,

02:45.692 --> 02:47.926
but you do understand
that biologically

02:47.961 --> 02:50.028
this isn't your child.
Of course I do.

02:50.063 --> 02:51.930
Okay.

02:51.965 --> 02:53.176
But I was thinking
we would have at least

02:53.200 --> 02:55.300
one child of our own.

02:55.335 --> 02:57.469
At least?

02:57.504 --> 03:00.105
At least.

03:00.140 --> 03:01.106
You were right, Louis.

03:01.141 --> 03:03.575
Getting to know each other
is fun.

03:05.345 --> 03:08.313
<i>[gentle music]</i>

03:08.348 --> 03:10.982
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:11.018 --> 03:12.918
Good, you're here.
I need your help.

03:12.953 --> 03:14.798
Is this about the worker comp
case from Flushing?

03:14.822 --> 03:17.856
No, this is about
Velocity Data Solutions.

03:17.891 --> 03:20.025
- What about them?
- They're a dirty company.

03:20.060 --> 03:21.805
They've been getting away
with shit for years.

03:21.829 --> 03:23.840
I could never go after them
when I worked at Pearson Specter

03:23.864 --> 03:25.742
because we were always on
the other side of these things,

03:25.766 --> 03:28.767
but I can go after them now.

03:28.802 --> 03:31.303
Mike, if this is going
to require me going to court--

03:31.338 --> 03:34.239
It's not.

03:34.274 --> 03:39.010
Look, Oliver, I know
what happened the other day.

03:39.046 --> 03:42.013
But you don't have to be a trial
lawyer to be a great lawyer.

03:42.049 --> 03:43.459
- What are you saying?
- I'm saying that you have

03:43.483 --> 03:45.183
skills that
other lawyers don't have

03:45.219 --> 03:48.620
and I'm gonna put those skills
to use right now.

03:48.655 --> 03:51.389
- What do you need?
- You see those boxes?

03:51.425 --> 03:54.059
That's every case that Velocity
has settled in the last 20 years

03:54.094 --> 03:55.872
where the names of
the plaintiffs have been sealed.

03:55.896 --> 03:57.596
We need to figure out
who those people are,

03:57.631 --> 03:59.471
what they got paid not to say,
and then we need

03:59.499 --> 04:02.434
to get every damn one of them
to come forward.

04:02.469 --> 04:04.069
Mike, what did
these guys do to you?

04:04.104 --> 04:05.481
They didn't do anything
to me, Oliver.

04:05.505 --> 04:06.883
I just don't like it when
people think they can get away

04:06.907 --> 04:09.341
with anything just because
nobody is watching.

04:14.381 --> 04:16.514
- That was fast.
- What was fast?

04:16.550 --> 04:17.515
Well, I assume you're here
to tell me

04:17.551 --> 04:18.884
you filed suit against Velocity.

04:18.918 --> 04:20.752
What I'm here
to tell you, Craig,

04:20.786 --> 04:22.821
is Mike Ross
is gonna handle Velocity.

04:22.856 --> 04:24.634
Then we have a problem,
'cause I didn't cut a deal

04:24.658 --> 04:26.102
with Mike Ross.
I cut a deal with you.

04:26.126 --> 04:28.093
And there's a reason
you're an in-house counsel

04:28.128 --> 04:30.295
and I'm not.
What are you talking about?

04:30.330 --> 04:32.163
Once we drop
whatever bomb we're gonna drop,

04:32.199 --> 04:34.377
they're gonna want to settle
without an admission of guilt

04:34.401 --> 04:36.668
and everyone knows
settling is what I do.

04:36.703 --> 04:38.637
So Mike Ross is gonna
take this to court?

04:38.672 --> 04:39.905
He's not even
a goddamn lawyer.

04:39.940 --> 04:41.606
Welcome to the conversation,
Craig.

04:41.642 --> 04:42.819
That's what I'm here
to talk about.

04:42.843 --> 04:44.876
You're gonna make
Mike's hearing official.

04:44.912 --> 04:46.578
I can't do that,
it's too soon.

04:46.613 --> 04:47.853
Bullshit.
You think I don't know

04:47.881 --> 04:50.081
you only said yes about Mike
to get me to help you?

04:50.117 --> 04:52.050
Of course that's why
I said yes.

04:52.085 --> 04:53.963
And the hardest thing about
getting him into the Bar

04:53.987 --> 04:56.499
is getting him a hearing when he
hasn't even gone to law school.

04:56.523 --> 04:58.390
Which is why you're
gonna sponsor him

04:58.425 --> 05:00.525
based on his years
of work at Pearson Specter.

05:00.560 --> 05:02.060
You're talking about
reading the law.

05:02.095 --> 05:03.061
You're damn right I am.

05:03.096 --> 05:05.330
There's precedent
and you know it.

05:05.365 --> 05:08.300
Listen to me,
I can influence the vote,

05:08.335 --> 05:10.635
but I cannot sponsor someone
I'm going to be voting on.

05:10.671 --> 05:12.003
Then find someone who will.

05:12.039 --> 05:13.917
Because if you can't get him
a hearing in the next week,

05:13.941 --> 05:14.906
this thing is off.

05:14.942 --> 05:16.241
And one more thing, Craig.

05:16.276 --> 05:17.943
You and I won't be
talking again

05:17.978 --> 05:19.844
because in case you haven't
figured it out yet,

05:19.880 --> 05:21.479
this is a hell of a lot
more serious

05:21.515 --> 05:23.548
than cheating on your wife.

